HEADWORD: Lactamide
<hw>Lac*tam"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lac</ets>tic
+ <ets>ami</ets>de.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An acid amide derived
from lactic acid, and obtained as a white crystalline substance having a
neutral reaction. It is metameric with alanine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

